Jan 31 (Reuters) - Wall Street's main indexes opened higher on Tuesday after wage growth data pointed to easing inflation ahead of the Federal Reserve's decision on interest rates. The Dow Jones Industrial Average (.DJI) rose 86.47 points, or 0.26%, at the open to 33,803.56. The S&P 500 (.SPX) opened higher by 3.08 points, or 0.08%, at 4,020.85, while the Nasdaq Composite (.IXIC) gained 4.76 points, or 0.04%, to 11,398.58 at the opening bell. Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.